body:
Hello,

Icarus seems to behave strangely when it encounters enumerated name to be assigned to an enum variable as a part of ternary operator. The following SystemVerilog code

```
module test;
  logic a;
  enum logic { S0, S1 } b;

  always_comb
    b = a ? S0 : S1;
endmodule
```

throws

`test.sv:6: error: This assignment requires an explicit cast.`

message and fails to compile. Casting it explicitly does the trick indeed, but it doesn't seem to make much sense and I couldn't find anything in IEEE1800-2012 that would call for an explicit cast in such assignment.

This seems to happen only when both enum and ?: come together, since the following compiles without any errors:

```
module test;
  logic a;
  enum logic { S0, S1 } b;
  logic c;

  always_comb begin
    if (a) b = S0;
    else   b = S1;
    
    c = a ? '0 : '1;
  end
endmodule
```

I could reproduce this in 12.0 stable and in current master. In all cases -g2012 option was used.

This behaviour was mentioned by jotego in #452, but since the issue itself was unrelated and labeled as Enhancement, I decided to make a new one.

